<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1229,2009]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,1481,1506]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Differential Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar in dorsal habitus to 
<taxonomicName box="[781,885,1481,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takutu">
<emphasis box="[781,885,1481,1505]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">H. takutu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[939,1053,1481,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hintoni">
<emphasis box="[939,1053,1481,1505]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">H. hintoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1068,1204,1481,1505]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 16" captionStart-1="FIGURE 17" captionStart-2="FIGURE 18" captionStartId-0="81.[151,250,1650,1673]" captionStartId-1="82.[151,250,1650,1673]" captionStartId-2="83.[151,250,1628,1651]" captionTargetBox-0="[228,1355,193,1626]" captionTargetBox-1="[238,1348,193,1626]" captionTargetBox-2="[246,1343,212,1586]" captionTargetId-0="figure@81.[228,1359,193,1629]" captionTargetId-1="figure@82.[238,1348,193,1629]" captionTargetId-2="figure@83.[226,1360,193,1607]" captionTargetPageId-0="81" captionTargetPageId-1="82" captionTargetPageId-2="83" captionText-0="FIGURE 16. Hydraena curvosa, holotype, dorsal and lateral habitus, and venter." captionText-1="FIGURE 17. Hydraena takutu, holotype, dorsal and lateral habitus, and venter." captionText-2="FIGURE 18. Hydraena hintoni, holotype, dorsal and lateral habitus, and venter." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/1050078/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/1050080/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/1050082/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Figs. 
<number box="[1131,1204,1481,1505]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="17.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="16.0">16–18</number>
</figureCitation>
); differentiated from both species by the more transverse pronotum that is more markedly sinuate laterally, and the very convex elytra. The metaventral plaques are carinate, similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[790,903,1553,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hintoni">
<emphasis box="[790,903,1553,1577]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">H. hintoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, the hind tibiae of males differ markedly in the two species. The male genitalia of the three species also show a relationship (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1236,1589,1613]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 15" captionStartId="80.[151,264,1650,1673]" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 15. Aedeagi of holotypes." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs. 15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1248,1323,1589,1613]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 20" captionStartId="84.[151,264,1650,1673]" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 20. Aedeagi of holotypes." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
19– 
<number box="[1292,1323,1589,1613]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
